<body>
    <h1>Installation Guide for Unix-Based Systems</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"contentLayout2">=20
<div class=3D"columnLayout two-right-sidebar" data-layout=3D"two-right-side=
bar">=20
<div class=3D"cell normal" data-type=3D"normal">=20
<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<h2 id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSystems-1.InstallaLAMPStack(*NIX,Ap=
ache,MySQL,PHP5+)">1. Install a LAMP Stack (*NIX, Apache, MySQL, PHP5+)</h2=
>
<p>Depending on your selected *NIX distribution, you may need to install pa=
rt or all of the LAMP stack required to run eZ Platform or eZ Enterprise. B=
efore getting started, make sure you review our <a href=3D"https://doc.ez.n=
o/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D31429536" rel=3D"nofollow">requirements</a=
> page to see the systems we support and use for testing. You can try using=
 an unsupported configuration, but your results may vary.</p>
<p>Please not that, while OS X <em>is</em> a *NIX-based system, it has its =
own unique requirements listed in our&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/DEVELOPER/In=
stallation+Guide+for+OS+X">Installation Guide for OS X</a>. Developer-maint=
ained installation notes are kept in our GitHub repository at this location=
 as well:&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezplatform/blob/mast=
er/INSTALL.md" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://github.com/=
ezsystems/ezplatform/blob/master/INSTALL.md</a></p>
<p>You may use your system's package manager (yum, apt-get, etc.) to obtain=
 a copy of Apache, MySQL, and PHP, or download the latest versions from the=
 official websites and install manually:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href=3D"https://httpd.apache.org/download.cgi" class=3D"external-lin=
k" rel=3D"nofollow">Apache2</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/" class=3D"external-lin=
k" rel=3D"nofollow">MySQL</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"http://php.net" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">PHP=
 5.6+</a></li>
</ul>
<p>For Debian 8.5, for example, we'd recommend using <code>apt-get</code> t=
o install <code>apache2</code>, <code>mysql-server</code>, <code>mysql-clie=
nt</code>, and <code>php5-*</code> (all the packages listed in the <a href=
=3D"https://doc.ez.no/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=3D31429536" rel=3D"nofol=
low">requirements</a>), as well as <code>git</code> for version control. If=
 the system on which you're doing the install has only 1 or 2 GB of RAM, be=
 sure to <a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/DEVELOPER/Set+up+Swap+on+Debi=
an+8.x" rel=3D"nofollow">set up swap</a> so you don't run out of RAM when r=
unning the composer scripts later on.</p>
<h2 id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSystems-2.GetComposer">2. Get Compo=
ser</h2>
<p>You'll need Composer, the PHP command line dependency manager.</p>
<p>a. Install Composer by running the following command on the terminal of =
the machine upon which you're installing eZ Platform:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">php -r "readfile('https://getcomposer.org/installer');" | php</pre=
>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>b. Move the downloaded composer.phar file to a globally-available path:<=
/p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">mv composer.phar /usr/local/bin/composer</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSystems-3.Downloadthedesiredversion=
ofeZPlatformoreZEnterprise">3. Download the desired version of eZ Platform =
or eZ Enterprise</h2>
<ul>
<li>If you are installing eZ Platform, download the latest archive from&nbs=
p;<a href=3D"http://share.ez.no/latest" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofo=
llow">http://share.ez.no/latest</a></li>
<li>For licensed eZ Enterprise customers, download your file here:&nbsp;<a =
href=3D"https://support.ez.no/Downloads" style=3D"line-height: 1.42857;" cl=
ass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://support.ez.no/Downloads</a><=
/li>
</ul>
<p>Expand the archive into <code>/var/www/ezplatform</code> or the folder n=
ame or your choosing.</p>
<p>For developers interested in working with the latest version of eZ Platf=
orm, you may also clone the latest from our GitHub repository:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">cd /var/www
git clone https://github.com/ezsystems/ezplatform.git /var/www/ezplatform</=
pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>You can rename the destination folder to whatever you like. This is wher=
e eZ Platform will live, and you'll point your virtual host to this folder =
to use as its root. You may choose to download an archive file&nbsp;from&nb=
sp;<a href=3D"http://share.ez.no/downloads/downloads" class=3D"external-lin=
k" rel=3D"nofollow">share.ez.no/downloads</a>&nbsp;instead of cloning from =
GitHub, and&nbsp;extract the eZ Platform&nbsp;archive to a similar director=
y. The subsequent steps are identical, regardless of the method you choose =
to obtain eZ Platform.</p>
<h2 id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSystems-4.CreateanewdatabaseforeZPl=
atform">4. Create a new database for eZ Platform</h2>
<p>Create new database (you can substitute&nbsp;<code>ezplatform</code>&nbs=
p;with the database name you want to use, but keep it in mind as you run th=
e installation script):</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">/usr/bin/mysql -u root -e 'create database ezplatform;'</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSystems-5.RuntheInstallationScripts=
">5. Run the Installation Scripts</h2>
<p>Composer will look inside the composer.json file and install all of the =
required packages to run eZ Platform. There's a script in the app folder ca=
lled console that will install eZ Platform for your desired environment as =
well (dev/prod).</p>
<p>This is the step where you want to make sure you have <a href=3D"https:/=
/doc.ez.no/display/DEVELOPER/Set+up+Swap+on+Debian+8.x" rel=3D"nofollow">sw=
ap configured for your machine</a> if it does not have an abundance of RAM.=
</p>
<h3 id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSystems-a.Runcomposerinstall:">a. R=
un composer install:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">cd /var/www/ezplatform
php -d memory_limit=3D-1 /usr/local/bin/composer install</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Once the installer gets to the point that it creates <code>app/config/pa=
rameters.yml</code>, you will be presented with a few decisions. The first =
asks you to choose a <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/reference/co=
nfiguration/framework.html#secret" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"=
>secret</a>; choose any random string you like, made up of characters, numb=
ers, and symbols, up to around 32 characters. This is used by Symfony when =
generating <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/book/forms.html#forms-=
csrf" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">CSRF tokens</a>, <a href=3D"=
http://symfony.com/doc/current/cookbook/security/remember_me.html" class=3D=
"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">encrypting cookies</a>, and for creating s=
igned URIs when using <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/book/http_c=
ache.html#edge-side-includes" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">ESI =
(Edge Side Includes)</a>.</p>
<p>Next, you'll be asked to specify a database driver. You may press return=
 to accept the default for this option, as well as the next several (<code>=
database_host, database_port, database_name, database_user</code>) unless y=
ou have customized those values and need to enter them as configured on you=
r installation. If you set a password for your database user, enter it when=
 prompted for <code>database_password</code>. The installer should continue=
 once you've completed this manual portion of the installation process.</p>
<h3 id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSystems-b.RuneZPlatform'sinstaller:=
">b. Run eZ Platform's installer:</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">php -d memory_limit=3D-1 /var/www/ezplatform/app/console ezplatform=
:install --env prod clean</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Don't forget to substitute any custom folder name you may have chosen in=
 place of <code>ezplatform/</code> after <code>/var/www/</code> in the exam=
ples above. As you can see, this example shows a clean production installat=
ion. We're telling PHP to run Symfony's console to execute the ezplatform i=
nstall script. You can get an informative output to learn more about the co=
nsole script's capabilities by swapping in these parameters:&nbsp;<code> co=
nfig:dump-reference ezpublish </code></p>
<p>If Composer asks you for your token, you must log in to your GitHub acco=
unt and edit your profile. Go to the Personal access tokens link and Genera=
te new token with default settings. Be aware that the token will be shown o=
nly once, so do not refresh the page until you paste the token into the Com=
poser prompt. This operation is performed only once when you install eZ Pla=
tform for the first time.</p>
<p>Please note that a clean install of eZ Platform doesn=E2=80=99t include =
the DemoBundle anymore.</p>
<h2 id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSystems-6.Setupthefolderrights(*NIX=
users)">6. Setup the folder rights (*NIX users)</h2>
<p>Like most things, <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/book/install=
ation.html#checking-symfony-application-configuration-and-setup" class=3D"e=
xternal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Symfony documentation</a> applies here, mean=
ing <code>app/cache</code> and <code>app/logs</code> need to be writable by=
 cli and web server user.</p>
<p>Furthermore, future files and directories created by these two users wil=
l need to inherit those access rights. <em>For security reasons, there is n=
o need for web server to have access to write to other directories.</em></p=
>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-tip=
">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-approve confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
Then, go to the=20
<a href=3D"/display/DEVELOPER/Setup+folder+rights">Setup folder rights</a> =
page for the next steps of this settings.
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSystems-7.SetupaVirtualHost">7. Set=
 up a Virtual Host</h2>
<p>For our example, we'll demonstrate using Apache2 as part of the traditio=
nal LAMP stack.</p>
<h3 style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;" id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSyst=
ems-OptionA:ScriptedConfiguration">Option A: Scripted Configuration</h3>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">Instead of manually editing the vhost.tem=
plate file, you may instead&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://doc.ez.no/display/DEVEL=
OPER/Web+Server" rel=3D"nofollow">use the included shell script</a>: /var/w=
ww/ezplatform/bin/vhost.sh to generate a configured .conf file.&nbsp;Check =
out the source of&nbsp;<code>vhost.sh</code>&nbsp;to see the options provid=
ed. Additional information is included in our&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/DEVE=
LOPER/Web+Server">Web Server</a>&nbsp;documentation here as well.</p>
<h3 style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;" id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSyst=
ems-OptionB:ManualEdits">Option B: Manual Edits</h3>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">a. Copy the vhost template file from its =
home in the doc folder:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">cp /var/www/ezplatform/doc/apache2/vhost.template /etc/apache2/sit=
es-available/ezplatform.conf</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">b. Edit the file, substituting the %place=
holders% with the appropriate values for your desired config:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">vi /etc/apache2/sites-available/ezplatform.conf</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">For a DEV environment, you can change</p>
<ul>
<li style=3D"list-style-type: none;background-image: none;">
<ul>
<li><code>&lt;VirtualHost %IP_ADDRESS%:%PORT%&gt;<br> </code>to<br> <code>&=
lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;</code></li>
<li><code>ServerName %HOST_NAME%<br>to<br>ServerName localhost</code></li>
<li><code>ServerAlias %HOST_ALIAS%<br>...that can simply be deleted.</code>=
</li>
<li><code>DocumentRoot %BASEDIR%/web<br>to<br>DocumentRoot /var/www/ezplatf=
orm/web</code></li>
<li><code>LimitRequestBody %BODY_SIZE_LIMIT%<br>to<br>LimitRequestBody 0</c=
ode></li>
<li><code>TimeOut %TIMEOUT%<br>to<br>TimeOut 42<br>to avoid waiting longer =
than 42 seconds for all the things.</code></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">Be sure to specify <code style=3D"line-he=
ight: 1.42857;">/var/www/ezplatform/web</code> as the <code style=3D"line-h=
eight: 1.42857;">DocumentRoot</code> and <code style=3D"line-height: 1.4285=
7;">Directory</code>. Uncomment the line that starts with #if[SYMFONY_ENV] =
and set the value, something like this:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;"># Environment.
# Possible values: "prod" and "dev" out-of-the-box, other values possible w=
ith proper configuration
# Defaults to "prod" if omitted (uses SetEnvIf so value can be used in rewr=
ite rules)
SetEnvIf Request_URI ".*" SYMFONY_ENV=3Ddev</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSystems-8.ServerConfiguration(Apach=
easexample)">8. Server Configuration (Apache as example)</h2>
<p>Make sure you've got the <code>libapache2-mod-php5</code> module install=
ed for Apache2 to use PHP5.x, and have the rewrite module enabled:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">apt-get -y install libapache2-mod-php5
a2enmod rewrite</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>a. You'll need the web user set as the owner/group on all your files to =
avoid a 500 error:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/ezplatform</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>b. With your vhost file properly prepared and located in /etc/apache2/si=
tes-available/ezplatform.conf, enable the VirtualHost and disable the defau=
lt:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">a2ensite ezplatform
a2dissite 000-default.conf</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"InstallationGuideforUnix-BasedSystems-9.Restartserver(Apache)">9.=
 Restart server (Apache)</h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">service apache2 restart</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
</div>=20
</div>=20
